  <data key="d17">efore a gloss on Galatians 5:20 says that "strifes are when persons strike one another through anger ." Hence strife is a kind of private war , because it takes place between private persons , being declared not by public authority, but rather by an inordinate will. Therefore strife is always sinful</data>
