  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a008.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Now it is evident, in accordance with what has been said ( Article 7 ), that it is charity which directs the acts of all other virtues to the last end, and which, consequently, also gives the form to all other acts of virtue : and it is precisely in this sense that charity is called the form of the virtues , for these are called virtues in relation to "informed" acts.</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
