  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q010.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Unbelief may be taken in two ways: first, by way of pure negation, so that a man be called an unbeliever, merely because he has not the faith . Secondly, unbelief may b</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q010" target="st.ii-ii.q010.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a001">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a001</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q010</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.10 — Unbelief in general</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q010.a001</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.10 a.1 — Is unbelief a sin?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q010.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Unbelief may be taken in two ways: first, by way of pure negation, so that a man be called an unbeliever, merely because he has not the faith . Secondly, unbelief may be taken by way of opposition to the faith ; in which</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q010" target="st.ii-ii.q010.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q010</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.10 — Unbelief in general</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q010.a002</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.10 a.2 — What is its subject?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q010.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( I-II:74:1 ; I-II:74:2 ), sin is said to be in the power which is the principle of the sinful act. Now a sinful act may have two principles: one is its first and universal principle, which commands all a</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q010" target="st.ii-ii.q010.a003" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a003">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a003</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q010</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.10 — Unbelief in general</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q010.a003</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.10 a.3 — Is it the greatest of sins?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q010.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Every sin consists formally in aversion from God , as stated above ( I-II:71:6 ; I-II:73:3 ). Hence the more a sin severs man from God , the graver it is. Now man is more than ever separated from God by unbelief, because</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q010" target="st.ii-ii.q010.a004" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a004">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a004</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q010</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.10 — Unbelief in general</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q010.a004</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.10 a.4 — Is every action of unbelievers a sin?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q010.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( I-II:85:2 ; I-II:85:4 ) mortal sin takes away sanctifying grace , but does not wholly corrupt the good of nature . Since therefore, unbelief is a mortal sin , unbelievers are without grace indeed, yet s</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q010" target="st.ii-ii.q010.a005" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a005">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a005</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q010</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.10 — Unbelief in general</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q010.a005</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.10 a.5 — The species of unbelief</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q010.a005.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( I-II:55:4 ; I-II:64:1 ), every virtue consists in following some rule of human knowledge or operation. Now conformity to a rule happens one way in one matter , whereas a breach of the rule happens in ma</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q010" target="st.ii-ii.q010.a006" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a006">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a006</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q010</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.10 — Unbelief in general</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q010.a006</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.10 a.6 — Their comparison, one with another</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q010.a006.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 5 ), two things may be considered in unbelief. One of these is its relation to faith : and from this point of view, he who resists the faith after accepting it, sins more grievously against fait</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q010" target="st.ii-ii.q010.a007" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a007">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a007</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q010</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.10 — Unbelief in general</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q010.a007</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.10 a.7 — Should we dispute about faith with unbelievers?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q010.a007.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">In disputing about the faith , two things must be observed: one on the part of the disputant; the other on the part of his hearers. On the part of the disputant, we must consider his intention . For if he were to dispute</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q010" target="st.ii-ii.q010.a008" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a008">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a008</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q010</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.10 — Unbelief in general</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q010.a008</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.10 a.8 — Should they be compelled to the faith?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q010.a008.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Among unbelievers there are some who have never received the faith , such as the heathens and the Jews : and these are by no means to be compelled to the faith , in order that they may believe , because to believe depend</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q010" target="st.ii-ii.q010.a009" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a009">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q010.contains.st.ii-ii.q010.a009</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q010</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.10 — Unbelief in general</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q010.a009</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.10 a.9 — Should we have communications with them?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
