  <data key="d17">Acts and habits are specified by their objects, as shown above ( I-II:18:2 ; I-II:54:2 ). Now the proper object of love is the good , as stated above ( I-II:27:1 ), so that wherever there is a special aspect of good , th</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q023" target="st.ii-ii.q023.a005" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a005">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a005</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q023</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.23 — Charity, considered in itself</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q023.a005</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.23 a.5 — Is it one virtue?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a005.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Charity , as stated above ( Article 1 ) is a kind of friendship of man for God . Now the different species of friendship are differentiated, first of all, in respect of a diversity of end, and in this way there are three</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q023" target="st.ii-ii.q023.a006" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a006">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a006</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q023</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.23 — Charity, considered in itself</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q023.a006</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.23 a.6 — Is it the greatest of the virtues?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a006.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Since good , in human acts , depends on their being regulated by the due rule, it must needs be that human virtue , which is a principle of good acts, consists in attaining the rule of human acts . Now the rule of human </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q023" target="st.ii-ii.q023.a007" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a007">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a007</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q023</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.23 — Charity, considered in itself</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q023.a007</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.23 a.7 — Is any true virtue possible without it?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a007.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Virtue is ordered to the good , as stated above ( I-II:55:4 ). Now the good is chiefly an end, for things directed to the end are not said to be good except in relation to the end. Accordingly, just as the end is twofold</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q023" target="st.ii-ii.q023.a008" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a008">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a008</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q023</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.23 — Charity, considered in itself</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q023.a008</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.23 a.8 — Is it the form of the virtues?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a008.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">In morals the form of an act is taken chiefly from the end. The reason of this is that the principal of moral acts is the will , whose object and form, so to speak, are the end. Now the form of an act always follows from</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q024" target="concept.charity" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q024.treated_in.concept.charity">
