  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q024.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Since, as stated in I:80:2 , the appetite is twofold, namely the sensitive, and the intellective which is called the will , the object of each is the good , but in different ways: for the object of the sensitive appetite is a good apprehended by sense, whereas the object of the in</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
