  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q031.a003</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.31 a.3 — Should we be more beneficent to those who are more closely united to us?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q031.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Grace and virtue imitate the order of nature , which is established by Divine wisdom. Now the order of nature is such that every natural agent pours forth its activity first and most of all on the things which are neares</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q031" target="st.ii-ii.q031.a004" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q031.contains.st.ii-ii.q031.a004">
