  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q032.a010</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.32 a.10 — How should alms be given?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q032.a010.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Alms may be considered abundant in relation either to the giver, or to the recipient: in relation to the giver, when that which a man gives is great as compared with his means. To give thus is praiseworthy, wherefore Our</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q033" target="concept.charity" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q033.treated_in.concept.charity">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q033.treated_in.concept.charity</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q033</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.33 — Fraternal correction</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.charity</data>
  <data key="d12">Charity</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q033-treated-in-concept-charity-st-ii-ii-q033-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q033.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ner. Now to do away with anyone's evil is the same as to procure his good : and to procure a person's good is an act of charity , whereby we wish and do our friend well. Consequently fraternal correction also is an act of charity , because thereby we drive out our brother's evil , viz.</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q033" target="concept.fraternal_correction" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q033.treated_in.concept.fraternal_correction">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q033.treated_in.concept.fraternal_correction</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q033</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.33 — Fraternal correction</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.fraternal_correction</data>
  <data key="d12">Fraternal Correction</data>
  <data key="d13">act_type</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q033-treated-in-concept-fraternal-correction-st-ii-ii-q033-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q033.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">n of a wrongdoer is twofold, one which applies a remedy to the sin considered as an evil of the sinner himself. This is fraternal correction properly so called, which is directed to the amendment of the sinner. Now to do away with anyone's evil is the same as to procure his good : and to procure a p</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q033" target="st.ii-ii.q033.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a001">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a001</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q033</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.33 — Fraternal correction</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q033.a001</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.33 a.1 — Is fraternal correction an act of charity?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q033.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">The correction of the wrongdoer is a remedy which should be employed against a man's sin . Now a man's sin may be considered in two ways, first as being harmful to the sinner, secondly as conducing to the harm of others,</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q033" target="st.ii-ii.q033.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q033</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.33 — Fraternal correction</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q033.a002</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.33 a.2 — Is it a matter of precept?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q033.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Fraternal correction is a matter of precept. We must observe, however, that while the negative precepts of the Law forbid sinful acts, the positive precepts inculcate acts of virtue . Now sinful acts are evil in themselv</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q033" target="st.ii-ii.q033.a003" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a003">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a003</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q033</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.33 — Fraternal correction</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q033.a003</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.33 a.3 — Does this precept bind all, or only superiors?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q033.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 1 ), correction is twofold. One is an act of charity , which seeks in a special way the recovery of an erring brother by means of a simple warning: such like correction belongs to anyone who has</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q033" target="st.ii-ii.q033.a004" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a004">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a004</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q033</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.33 — Fraternal correction</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q033.a004</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.33 a.4 — Does this precept bind the subject to correct his superior?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q033.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">A subject is not competent to administer to his prelate the correction which is an act of justice through the coercive nature of punishment: but the fraternal correction which is an act of charity is within the competenc</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q033" target="st.ii-ii.q033.a005" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a005">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a005</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q033</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.33 — Fraternal correction</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q033.a005</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.33 a.5 — May a sinner correct anyone?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q033.a005.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 3, Reply to Objection 2 ), to correct a wrongdoer belongs to a man, in so far as his reason is gifted with right judgment. Now sin , as stated above ( I-II:85:1 ; I-II:85:2 ), does not destroy t</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q033" target="st.ii-ii.q033.a006" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a006">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a006</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q033</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.33 — Fraternal correction</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q033.a006</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.33 a.6 — Should one correct a person who becomes worse through being corrected?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q033.a006.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 3 ) the correction of the wrongdoer is twofold. One, which belongs to prelates , and is directed to the common good , has coercive force. Such correction should not be omitted lest the person co</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q033" target="st.ii-ii.q033.a007" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a007">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a007</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q033</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.33 — Fraternal correction</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q033.a007</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.33 a.7 — Should secret correction precede denouncement?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q033.a007.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">With regard to the public denunciation of sins it is necessary to make a distinction: because sins may be either public or secret. On the case of public sins , a remedy is required not only for the sinner, that he may be</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q033" target="st.ii-ii.q033.a008" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a008">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q033.contains.st.ii-ii.q033.a008</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q033</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.33 — Fraternal correction</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q033.a008</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.33 a.8 — Should witnesses be called before denouncement?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q033.a008.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">The right way to go from one extreme to another is to pass through the middle space. Now Our Lord wished the beginning of fraternal correction to be hidden, when one brother corrects another between this one and himself </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q034" target="concept.charity" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q034.treated_in.concept.charity">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q034.treated_in.concept.charity</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q034</data>
