  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a004</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.4 — Can the object of faith be anything seen?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a004-treated-in-concept-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a004-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Faith implies assent of the intellect to that which is believed</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a004" target="concept.object_of_faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a004.treated_in.concept.object_of_faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a004.treated_in.concept.object_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a004</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.4 — Can the object of faith be anything seen?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.object_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Object of Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">doctrine</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a004-treated-in-concept-object-of-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a004-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Faith implies assent of the intellect to that which is believed . Now the intellect assents to a thing in two ways. First, through being moved to assent by its very object, which is known either by itself (as in the case of first principles, which are held by</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a005" target="concept.faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a005.treated_in.concept.faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a005.treated_in.concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a005</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.5 — Can it be anything known?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a005-treated-in-concept-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a005-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a005.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">On like manner it may happen that what is an object of vision or scientific knowledge for one man , even in the state of a wayfarer, is, for another man , an object of faith , because he does not know it by demonstration</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a005" target="concept.object_of_faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a005.treated_in.concept.object_of_faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a005.treated_in.concept.object_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a005</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.5 — Can it be anything known?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.object_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Object of Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">doctrine</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a005-treated-in-concept-object-of-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a005-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a005.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">On like manner it may happen that what is an object of vision or scientific knowledge for one man , even in the state of a wayfarer, is, for another man , an object of faith , because he does not know it by demonstration</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a006" target="concept.article_of_faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a006.treated_in.concept.article_of_faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a006.treated_in.concept.article_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a006</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.6 — Should the things to be believed be divided into a certain number of articles?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.article_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Article of Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">doctrine</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a006-treated-in-concept-article-of-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a006-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a006.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">the word "article" is apparently derived from the Greek; for the Greek arthron [Cf. William of Auxerre , Summa Aurea] which the Latin renders "articulus," signifies a fitting together of distinct parts: wherefore the small parts of the body which fit together</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a006" target="concept.faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a006.treated_in.concept.faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a006.treated_in.concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a006</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.6 — Should the things to be believed be divided into a certain number of articles?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a006-treated-in-concept-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a006-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a006.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">iv) that an article is composed of words each pronounced singly and separately, thus: "Your passion, your voice, your look, have struck terror into your foes." Hence matters of Christian faith are said to contain distinct articles, in so far as they are divided into parts, and fit together</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a007" target="concept.article_of_faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a007.treated_in.concept.article_of_faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a007.treated_in.concept.article_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a007</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.7 — These articles: are they of faith for all times?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.article_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Article of Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">doctrine</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a007-treated-in-concept-article-of-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a007-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a007.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">The articles of faith stand in the same relation to the doctrine of faith , as self-evident principles to a teaching based on natural reason</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a007" target="concept.faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a007.treated_in.concept.faith">
